-- Motorola Solutions Opens Kenya Office for Enterprise Business
-- B y   J o h n s t o n e   O l e   T u r a n a
-- 2012-11-14T15:35:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-14/motorola-solutions-opens-kenya-office-for-enterprise-business.html
Motorola Solutions Inc. (MSI) , the maker
of two-way radios and barcode scanners, opened an office in
Kenya for its enterprise business.  “We seek to leverage on Kenya as a leading African
reformer in the information, communication and technology
sector,” Carlos Ferraz, strategy consultant at Motorola
Solutions Enterprise Mobility for Africa, told reporters today
in Nairobi, the capital. The regional office will cover sub-
Saharan Africa excluding South Africa, he said.  Motorola has provided its enterprise solutions to companies
including  Diageo Plc. (DGE) ’s Kenyan unit,  East African Breweries
Ltd. (EABL) ;  Kenya Airways Ltd. (KNAL) ; and the Kenya Ports Authority, Ferraz
said. It’s also targeting providing services regionally to its
global clients including DHL Worldwide Express, Shell Plc,
Unilever Plc, Coca Cola Co., Ferraz said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
